VALUES
(43, 15, 24, 40, 9, 33, 33, 'the works which none other man did', 'Miraculous Works and Reactions', 'Both passages emphasize the extraordinary works of Jesus that provoke strong reactions. In John, the works lead to hatred, while in Matthew, they inspire marvel among the multitudes.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 24, 58, 2, 3, 4, 'the works which none other man did', 'Connection of Signs and Works', 'This connection highlights the emphasis on miraculous works and signs. Both passages refer to the divine acts that confirm the message of Jesus, illustrating the rejection of His ministry despite the evidence presented.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 24, 2, 20, 5, 5, 'hated both me and my Father', 'Connection of Sin and Hatred', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hatred towards God and the consequences of sin. In John 15:24, the rejection of Jesus and the Father is linked to sin, while Exodus 20:5 speaks of visiting iniquity upon those who hate God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 24, 20, 8, 36, 36, 'hated both me and my Father', 'Connection of Sin and Hate', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of sin and hatred. John 15:24 speaks of hatred towards Jesus and the Father, while Proverbs 8:36 states that those who hate God love death, linking hatred with spiritual harm.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 25, 19, 109, 3, 3, 'hated me without a cause', 'Connection of Hatred Without Cause', 'Both passages emphasize being hated without justification. John 15:25 cites Psalms 109:3 to illustrate the fulfillment of this theme in the experience of Jesus.', 'quotation', 0.587, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 25, 19, 69, 4, 4, 'They hated me without a cause', 'Connection of Unjust Hatred', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being hated without cause. John 15:25 directly quotes the sentiment found in Psalms 69:4, highlighting the unjust animosity faced by the speaker.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 25, 42, 24, 44, 44, 'that the word might be fulfilled', 'Fulfillment of Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the fulfillment of what is written in the law. John 15:25 refers to hatred without cause, while Luke 24:44 speaks of all things that must be fulfilled concerning Jesus.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 25, 47, 11, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Suffering and Preaching', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering for the sake of others. Both passages emphasize the idea of being unjustly treated or abased while serving a greater purpose.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 25, 66, 21, 6, 6, 'hated me without a cause', 'Connection of Fulfillment and Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of fulfillment in God''s plan. Both passages emphasize the transition from rejection, as seen in ''hated me without a cause,'' to the promise of life and sustenance in ''fountain of the water of life.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 25, 43, 10, 34, 34, 'their law', 'Connection of Law and Rejection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of the law and the rejection of Jesus. In John 15:25, the hatred towards Jesus is linked to the fulfillment of what is written in their law, while John 10:34 references the law to assert Jesus'' identity. This connection highlights the tension between Jesus and the religious authorities regarding scriptural interpretation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 25, 45, 3, 19, 19, 'They hated me without a cause', 'Connection of Guilt and Hatred', 'This connection highlights the theme of guilt and condemnation present in both passages. John 15:25 speaks of hatred without cause, while Romans 3:19 emphasizes that all are guilty before God, suggesting a universal human condition of sin and rejection.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 26, 43, 14, 26, 26, NULL, 'Connection of the Comforter', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Comforter, identified as the Holy Ghost, who is sent by the Father. They highlight the Comforter''s functions of teaching and testifying about Jesus.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 26, 43, 14, 16, 17, 'the Spirit of truth', 'Connection of the Comforter', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Comforter as the Spirit of truth. They highlight the Comforter''s relationship with the Father and His presence with believers.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 26, 44, 5, 32, 32, 'he shall testify of me', 'Connection of the Holy Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit as a witness. John 15:26 mentions the Spirit testifying of Jesus, while Acts 5:32 states that the Holy Ghost is a witness to the apostles'' testimony.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 26, 44, 2, 32, 33, 'the Spirit of truth', 'Connection of the Holy Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit as a witness to Jesus. John 15:26 mentions the Spirit of truth testifying of Jesus, while Acts 2:32-33 describes the outpouring of the Holy Ghost as a fulfillment of that promise.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 26, 62, 5, 6, 10, NULL, 'Witness of the Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit as a witness to Jesus Christ. John 15:26 mentions the Spirit of truth testifying about Jesus, while 1 John 5:6-10 states that the Spirit bears witness because it is truth.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 26, 42, 24, 49, 49, NULL, 'Connection of the Comforter and Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the sending of the Spirit. John 15:26 mentions the Comforter, while Luke 24:49 refers to the promise of the Father, indicating a divine empowerment for the disciples.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 26, 46, 1, 6, 6, 'testify of me', 'Testimony of Christ Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of testimony in both passages. John 15:26 speaks of the Spirit testifying of Christ, while 1 Corinthians 1:6 mentions the confirmation of Christ''s testimony in believers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 27, 62, 4, 14, 14, 'bear witness', 'Witnessing and Testifying Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of bearing witness. John 15:27 speaks of the disciples bearing witness due to their experience with Jesus, while 1 John 4:14 asserts that they testify about the Father sending the Son.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 27, 43, 21, 24, 24, 'bear witness', 'Witness and Testimony Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the disciples as witnesses. In John 15:27, the disciples are called to bear witness, while John 21:24 affirms the truth of the testimony of a specific disciple.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 27, 44, 10, 39, 42, 'bear witness, because ye have been with me', 'Witnesses of Christ''s Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of bearing witness to Jesus'' life and resurrection. Both passages emphasize the role of those who were with Jesus, indicating their authority to testify about Him.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 27, 42, 24, 48, 48, 'bear witness', 'Witnesses of Christ''s Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the disciples as witnesses. John 15:27 states they will bear witness because of their close association with Jesus, while Luke 24:48 directly identifies them as witnesses of the events they experienced.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 27, 42, 1, 2, 3, 'from the beginning', 'Witnesses from the Beginning', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being ''from the beginning'' as eyewitnesses. This connection highlights the role of those who have directly experienced the ministry of Jesus and their responsibility to bear witness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 27, 44, 23, 11, 11, 'bear witness', 'Witnessing for Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of bearing witness. John 15:27 speaks of the disciples bearing witness due to their close relationship with Jesus, while Acts 23:11 highlights Paul''s testimony in Jerusalem and his future witness in Rome.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 27, 62, 1, 1, 2, 'bear witness', 'Witness and Manifestation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of bearing witness to Jesus'' life and teachings. Both passages emphasize the importance of firsthand experience with Jesus, as the disciples are called to witness due to their presence ''from the beginning.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
